    "category_validation": {
      "expected_category": "oneshot",
      "validated": true,
      "evidence_note": "Repo-wide validation at the pinned commit supports the oneshot category. Core non-test components use mpsc-style channels extensively: consensus startup wires timeout/self-message queues, mempool receives client and consensus requests, network/peer-manager code uses channel queues, state sync/inter-component notifications use futures mpsc, and the logger/storage components use std mpsc for worker threads. Pub-sub/event notification is architectural through state-sync event/reconfiguration subscriptions and inter-component consensus/mempool notifications, plus multiple subscriber channels in shared mempool. Oneshot is widely used for request/response callbacks in network RPC, peer manager/connectivity requests, consensus-to-mempool requests, state-sync clients, and notification acknowledgements. Competing consumers appear, but more narrowly, e.g. crossbeam cloned receivers in language/testing-infra/test-generation for worker threads; this looks like tooling rather than a dominant application architecture pattern."
    }
